$x$ | $g(x)$ | $h(x)$ | $g'(x)$
:-: | :-: | :-: | :-: 
$1$ | $-6$ | $3$ | $\dfrac12$
$3$ | $1$ | $2$ | $-2$

Let's plug in those values!

$\begin{align}
h'(1)&=\dfrac{1}{g'\Bigl(h(1)\Bigr)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{g'(3)}&&\gray{h(1)=3}
